		<p>Amazing fact number 12 is only half amazing. The fact, if true, that so many babies were named AoYun is quite interesting, but the calendar date had more to do with the desire to give birth than the Olympics did. In Chinese culture 8 is an auspicious number, and no date will have this many 8s auspiciously arranged (08/08/08) until 2088. Weddings are also often scheduled for August 8th of each year.</p>

